					<description><![CDATA[<p>UroMems, a worldwide leader in medical technology and mechatronic solutions for urology, has secured $60 million in a strategic round of funding. UroMems has raised its biggest funding ever to</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/uromems-raises-60m-for-smart-urology-implant-trials/" data-wpel-link="internal">UroMems Raises $60M for Smart Urology Implant Trials</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.uromems.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">UroMems</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, a worldwide leader in medical technology and mechatronic solutions for urology, has secured $60 million in a strategic round of </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/mantle8-raises-36m-for-natural-hydrogen-expansion/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. </span>UroMems has raised its biggest funding ever to fast-track regulatory and clinical development of its flagship product, UroActive®. Ajax Health Fund I, sponsored by ICONIQ Capital and sub-advised by Ajax Health, fully syndicated the investment.</p>
<p>UroMems builds momentum, having joined a $47M Series C completed mid-2024. With this latest round, the company has raised over $150M, positioning itself as a leader in SUI therapy.&#8221;</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Redefining Stress Urinary Incontinence Treatment</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Stress Urinary Incontinence (SUI) is a debilitating condition which causes patients to involuntarily leak urine when engaging in physical activities such as coughing, sneezing, or working out. It afflicts roughly 40 million Americans and 90 million Europeans. The traditional gold standard for treatment has been the manual artificial urinary sphincter, which is operated by having the patient manually squeeze the pump in their scrotum or labia to urinate.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201198" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201198" class="wp-image-201198 size-large" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/UroMems_Logo-1536x893-1-1024x595.jpeg" alt="UroMems Logo" width="1024" height="595" /><p id="caption-attachment-201198" class="wp-caption-text">Source: UroMems</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This is where UroActive sets itself apart from the rest. </span>UroActive is an active implantable electronic device built on a novel mechatronic platform using embedded smart, digital and robotic systems. The device maximizes user convenience and minimizes tissue atrophy or failure by automatically adjusting urethral pressure based on patient activity</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/mantle8-raises-36m-for-natural-hydrogen-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400"> Mantle8 Raises $36M for Natural Hydrogen Expansion</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Pivotal Trials and Global Regulatory Strategy</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $60 million investment will be used for the continued SOPHIA2 study, a milestone pivotal trial. This is a prospective multicenter study recruiting patients at 21 sites in the United States and France. It builds on robust initial feasibility data published for the first SOPHIA trial. This data showed a 100% successful implantation rate and notable symptom reduction in males and females.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The US Food and Drug Administration (FDA) granted an Investigational Device Exemption (IDE) for the SOPHIA2 trial, together with the French National Agency for the Safety of Medicines and Health Products (ANSM) approval in 2024. The data produced from the trial will form the main body of UroMems&#8217; submission to the FDA Pre-Market Approval (PMA) and to the European CE Mark.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Partnership with Ajax Health</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">What Ajax Health provides to UroMems extends beyond funding. </span>Seasoned Ajax medtech professionals have joined the UroMems Board of Directors alongside the investment. Their knowledge of growing disruptive medtech companies will be important as UroMems evolves from clinical to commercial stage.</p>
<p>The technology platform is backed by 200 issued patents protecting high-tech sensors and mechatronic components behind the &#8216;learning&#8217; device. The device adapts to each patient&#8217;s individual lifestyle. With SOPHIA2 study data not due till December 2026, UroMems is poised to impact a market unchanged for 50 years.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/uromems-raises-60m-for-smart-urology-implant-trials/" data-wpel-link="internal">UroMems Raises $60M for Smart Urology Implant Trials</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
