					<description><![CDATA[<p>Innovation leader in the emerging area of geologic hydrogen, Mantle8 announced that it raised $36 million (€31 million) in a Series A round. Funds will be used to promote the</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/mantle8-raises-36m-for-natural-hydrogen-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Mantle8 Raises $36M for Natural Hydrogen Expansion</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Innovation leader in the emerging area of geologic hydrogen, </span><a href="https://mantle8.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Mantle8 </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">announced that it raised $36 million (€31 million) in a Series A </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nvision-raises-55m-to-expand-quantum-healthcare-tech/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">round</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. Funds will be used to promote the company&#8217;s proprietary exploration platform and operations and for what is being billed as the world&#8217;s most advanced natural hydrogen drilling campaign.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sandwater led the funding round and saw participation from several big names in climate tech investment, including Breakthrough Energy Ventures (backed by Bill Gates), IP Group, Wind Capital and Calderion. The French government took part via Bpifrance in its Ecotechnologies 2 fund.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Shift Toward &#8220;Gold&#8221; Hydrogen</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most hydrogen used by industry has been derived from fossil sources (grey) or high-energy processes like electrolysis (green). Mantle8 more specifically targets natural sources of hydrogen (white or even gold). White hydrogen is discovered naturally in chemical reactions within the Earth&#8217;s crust.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201175" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201175" class="size-large wp-image-201175" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Gas-1024x683.jpg" alt="Gas" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-201175" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The goal of Mantle8 is to unlock these underground sources of energy that are part of a zero-carbon, no-water, no-large-scale renewable input supply, also needed to produce green hydrogen. Applying advanced geoscience to this problem, Mantle8 hopes to supply a cheaper, cleaner fuel source.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nvision-raises-55m-to-expand-quantum-healthcare-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">NVision Raises $55M to Expand Quantum Healthcare Tech</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Proprietary Technology and the &#8220;Geological Trifecta&#8221;</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The primary hurdle in the natural hydrogen sector has long been the difficulty of locating commercially viable accumulations. Mantle8 addresses this through its HOREX® technology, a multiphysics platform that produces 4D images of active underground hydrogen systems. This technology was recently validated at the Hydrogeco project in the French Pyrenees, where the company completed the world’s first 4D imaging of an active hydrogen system.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company&#8217;s exploration framework is built around a concept it calls the &#8220;Geological Trifecta&#8221;. This model identifies areas where three specific conditions converge:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">An active hydrogen-generating source (such as the oxidation of iron-rich rocks).</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">A continuous replenishment mechanism.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">A robust geological seal or trap that prevents the gas from escaping.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By focusing on these &#8220;active&#8221; systems rather than static deposits, Mantle8 believes it can ensure a sustained, long-term flow of gas.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Economic and Strategic Implications</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The economics for Mantle8 are disruptive. The estimated cost to produce the clean hydrogen would be as low as €0.80/kg. Green hydrogen prices are between €4 and €6, depending on location and energy prices. When comparing this price to natural hydrogen, it is competitive even without subsidies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For Europe, whether Mantle8 succeeds carries profound geopolitical implications. </span>As an area shifting away from imported natural gas reliance, domestic pure hydrogen offers a route to energy independence. The company will use the new capital to prioritise the best global sites and commence confirmatory drilling within 24 months</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
